message.content:
cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on mobile edge computing and offloading tasks from mobile devices to edge servers and cloud servers. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes an edge-cloud cooperative architecture for computation offloading. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a mixed integer programming model and algorithms to solve the computation offloading problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper aims to minimize energy consumption of mobile devices through computation offloading. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the deployment of edge servers at WiFi access points or cellular base stations.
